title: AC-15 — debug-stats sparse emission
story: channel-service-test
description: Drives the channel-service-test story through stdlib actions (look / take / drop) so the debug-stats channel exercises sparse-emit suppression on unchanged inventory.
---

# ============================================================================
# GOAL: validate the playable story works through the CLI bundle
# AC-15 sparse-emission semantics are validated separately by the
# in-process renderer-parity test in
# packages/channel-service/tests/ac-15-story-renderer-parity.test.ts
# ============================================================================

# Initial look — establishes the lab and the beacon.
> look
[OK: contains "The Lab"]
[OK: contains "beacon"]

# Re-look — same content, exercises sparse-emit suppression on the
# debug-stats channel (no inventory change between turns).
> look
[OK: contains "The Lab"]

# Take the beacon — inventory grows from 0 → 1.
> take beacon
[OK: contains "Taken"]

# Look again — the lab no longer lists the beacon among visible items
# (it's now in the player's inventory).
> look
[OK: contains "The Lab"]
[OK: not contains "see beacon here"]

# Drop the beacon — inventory shrinks from 1 → 0.
> drop beacon
[OK: contains "Dropped"]

# Final look — beacon visible again in the lab.
> look
[OK: contains "beacon"]
